				\begin{document}$$ F\left(\mathrm{a}\right)\approx {a}^{D_f} $$\end{document}

The uneven surface fractal dimension, Df, can be determined in an approach of Hausdorff dimension that is based on the relative size analysis of a similar unit. As the factor of forming cord surface, the convex district which includes several micro-convex structure units with different edges and number can be expressed as:
1-2M=NDf\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
