				\begin{document}$$ M={N}^{D_f} $$\end{document}

where M is the number of the convex unit, N is the repeated multiple self-similar units that is the length of convex units to the length of whole samples, and Df is the raised structuresâ fractal dimension. The equation is a model that can be used to predict the surface morphology, so:
